c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Levity and Pipedream share a solid foundation of core features including Visual Builder, Api Connections, Scheduling, Conditional Logic. Where Levity pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Ai Actions, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Pipedream uniquely offers Code Support and Error Handling, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Levity holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Pipedream scores 8/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Pipedream comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Levity begins at $49/mo. Pipedream stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Levity requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
