10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Levity is best suited for document processing, email classification, content moderation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Pipedream, meanwhile, shines for developers, API integrations, technical teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Levity describes itself as \"No-code AI workflow automation for classifying text, images, and documents.\" Pipedream, established in 2018, positions itself as \"Connect APIs with code-level control and serverless execution.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Pipedream** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Levity is a poor choice — far from it. Levity excels in its own right, particularly for document processing and email classification.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value full code support with node.js and python, go with Pipedream. If train custom ai classifiers without code matters more to you, Levity is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
